ion:
  id: 04-agent/handoff-packet
  title: handoff packet
  type: agent-template
  status: seed-canon
  updated: 2026-06-30

purpose:
  A handoff packet gives an agent enough context to continue a movement loop
  without inventing the frame.

packet:
  current_frame:
  active_lacuna:
  relevant_files:
  stability_state:
  chosen_move:
  proof_plan:
  boundaries:
  last_replay:
  open_questions:

handoff_rule:
  A handoff is valid only if it names what the agent may do, what it may not
  assume, and what proof would count as an update.

minimal_instruction:
  Read the linked files. Preserve the reality boundary. Help the human choose
  or complete one bounded move. Record proof. Replay changes.

proof:
  source:
    - 04-agent/agent-orientation-charter.ion
  claim: Agent continuity requires explicit frame, move, proof, and boundary context.
  proof_state: seed-backed
